        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> from [rust-lang/rust-analyzer#21737](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-analyzer/issues/21737)\r\n> \r\n> > It's probably not a good idea to try to 'automatically' detect the workspace without user input like Nvim seems to do.\r\n> \r\n> so... does this PR actually address that?\r\n\r\nI'm not going to argue with the decision made for rust-analyzer in lspconfig to find workspace root for user's projects. I actually think it's a good call. What it shouldn't do is to treat library sources as independent project. It should treat it as library and reuse existing lsp client. In order to do so detection logic needs to be fixed to recognize library sources in sysroot as library and that's what this PR tries to address.",
