            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> from [rust-lang/rust-analyzer#21737](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-analyzer/issues/21737)\r\n> \r\n> > It's probably not a good idea to try to 'automatically' detect the workspace without user input like Nvim seems to do.\r\n> \r\n> so... does this PR actually address that?\r\n\r\nIt does. By adding sysroot to the library detection, it effectively makes Neovim understand that the user is trying to go to definition.\r\n\r\nroslyn_ls uses a similar pattern:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/faa403f95fd82cc24ebd0cee6af41b0de2dae00c/lsp/roslyn_ls.lua#L157",
